        "timestamp": "2017-12-21 05:08:30.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHi Marcus, as per the rule when an integer arithmetic operation result is assigned to a long there may be loss of precision because the result may have already overflowed before the assignment. the compliant solution for this rule is at least one operand should be cast or promoted to the final type before the operation takes place.\nin this case i suggest use long literal \"1000L\" instead of explicit casting.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
